description: The FTSE Japanese Government Bond Index aims to reflect the performance of the following market: JPY-denominated bonds issued by the Japanese government Exposure across the whole yield curve (minimum time to maturity of 1 year) Minimum amount outstanding of JPY 500 billion; 20+ year bonds: JPY 450 billion (float adjustment: excludes Bank of Japan holdings and Ministry of Finance buybacks) Additional information on the Index and the general methodology behind the FTSE Russel indices can be found on FTSE Russel Index website ( https://www.yieldbook.com/ ).
name: Xtrackers II Japan Government Bond UCITS ETF 1C
